Text: Hello, My name is Louis Richards. How old am I, I am in my early 20s. How am I, I am well, thank you but my eyes hurt.

Reason for visit. The reason I have come for a sight test today, what brings me along, why I am here today, is because I have come for an exam (here) today because I am noticing that my eyes hurt and I'm getting headaches when I am studying for longer periods of time, and I was talking to my mum, and she told me I should get my eyes checked. This is my first ever proper eye test, although I did get my eyes checked at school. My eyes hurt, like an ache in the eye ball. I first noticed my eye's aching and the headaches about 2 months ago in the run up to an exam. The headache is right over my eyes. The headaches start after about 3 hours on the computer. I tried paracetamol for the headaches but they did nothing. I have not seen my doctor (GP) about the headaches. I think the eye ache and headaches are slowly getting worse.

I don't wear any glasses. I never have worn glasses, as I can see perfectly but recently, I have been getting this strain when I am studying. My distance vision is great. My near vision is awesome most of the time but it can go a little blurry after studying for a lot.

Any thing else, I am also looking at applying for the fire service after I graduate this year and I think you might need an up-to-date eye test for that as well. My dad was a firefighter, that's what got me interested in the idea of being a firefighter myself. I really want to be a firefighter.

I couldn't tell you when my last eye test was, I'm afraid, I know I was in primary school and that my mum took me if that's helpful? I know that I didn't need glasses or any patches that some other people in primary needed. I have never even broken a bone or been to the hospital, apart from to visit my grandad. I have not had to see a doctor about my eyes. I have not gone to a hospital because of my eyes. I don't see flashing lights and I don't have anything floating (floaters) around in my vision. I don't get any pain apart from the ache and my eyes are not red unless I have been up all night. I did not have an eye patched as a child.

My general health, I'm generally very healthy, I'm good, apart from smoking occasionally on nights out. I only smoke the odd cigarette. When I drink, I usually drink too much, I'm afraid. I have some allergies, mostly hay fever. I take antihistamines only in the summer for my hay fever, and I'm allergic to penicillin, but I have never had any issues with that. I don't have diabetes or any other health problems. My family is very healthy too, I don't think that any of them have any health issues.

Screens, I am aware I am probably using the screen too much, but I am a final year university student, and I don't think that I'll be able to cut the amount of time down soon. I spend about 10 hours a day on the computer, mostly studying but also playing games. My favourite game is CS go, it is a first person shooter. I also find that I am watching a lot of driving videos as I am learning to drive and want to pass first time! I'm learning to drive. Funny enough, I don't have a smart phone, I just have an old school phone with the buttons.

For a living, work, occupation, I am a student at University of Reading. I am a second year student and I am studying Philosophy. My favourite Philosopher is Plato, we all have to get out of our caves!
I don't know what I'm going to do for a living after I graduate exactly but I would quite like to be a firefighter like my dad if possible.

My family's eyes, my grandma has a problem with her eyes, I think it is called Blaucoma, no Glaucoma! But other than that, nothing else. Family eye problems, oh, and both my grandparents have had their cataracts out.  Family history, my parents are fine they just wear glasses for reading. No one in my family has diabetes, raised blood pressure or macular disease.

Hobbies, I like to try and get away from the screens when I am not revising and I do a lot of swimming (that's my main hobby), my friends call me the fish. I like to run too but I am not as good at that. When I am at home, and I can bring my dogs for runs with me I find that I am much quicker. I also find it easier to run in the summer, I like the warm more than the cold. At least with swimming its warm all year round.
I do not have anything else to say. I do not have anything more to add. Thank you.
